---
import HeroCard from "@/components/home/HeroCard.astro";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import AnimatedText from "@/components/ui/AnimatedText.astro";
---

<Layout
  title=" Zorro and Zorro: A Tale of Two Zorros Across Time"
  description="A fight against Spanish tyranny, Zorro serves the people to bring about justice and act as a symbol of hope."
>
  <div
    class="relative site-container z-20 w-full mx-auto mt-16 px-4 md:mt-18 lg:mt-20 xl:px-0"
  >
    <div
      class="relative w-full px-4 flex flex-col items-center justify-between md:flex-row mb-16"
    >
      <div
        class="relative w-full md:max-w-[420px] md:w-1/2 text-center sm:text-left sm:-mt-8"
      >
        <!-- Title - AnimatedText animation -->
        <h1 class="mb-4">
          <AnimatedText
            content="Zorro: A Symbol of Justice, Hope, and Charm"
            delay={0.1}
            duration={0.5}
            stagger={0.08}
            class="text-5xl text-pri leading-tight md:text-4xl lg:text-6xl font-brand"
          />
        </h1>

        <!-- First description - AnimatedText animation -->
        <div class="mb-2">
          <AnimatedText
            content="A fight against Spanish tyranny, Zorro serves the people to bring about justice and act as a symbol of hope. His charm captivates both allies and foes alike, and is a big part of his success and likability."
            delay={0.3}
            duration={0.5}
            stagger={0.015}
            class="text-base text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- HeroCard - AOS animation -->
      <div
        class="relative justify-end w-full mt-16 md:flex md:pl-10 md:w-1/2 md:mt-0 md:translate-y-4 xl:translate-y-0"
        data-aos="fade-left-sm"
        data-aos-delay="300"
        data-aos-duration="800"
        data-aos-once="true"
      >
        <HeroCard
          imageUrl="/assets/iconography/zorro-stance.jpg"
          title=""
          link=""
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section
    class="mt-26 mb-12"
    data-aos="fade-up-sm"
    data-aos-delay="100"
    data-aos-duration="600"
    data-aos-once="true"
  >
    <div class="site-container px-4 md:px-8">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
        <div class="w-72 md:w-80 mr-6">
          <HeroCard
            imageUrl="/assets/iconography/don-rafael.png"
            title="Spanish Governor Don Rafael Montero (1998)"
            link=""
          />
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Justice</h3>
          <p
            class="text-base text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4 text-balance"
          >
            Zorro is the masked identity of Don Diego de la Vega, who moonlights
            as this vigilante to combat the corruption from the ruling
            governor of Spanish California and to give peace to the peasants who are
            subjected to tyranny.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    class="mt-26 mb-12"
    data-aos="fade-up-sm"
    data-aos-delay="100"
    data-aos-duration="600"
    data-aos-once="true"
  >
    <div class="site-container px-4 md:px-8">
      <div class="flex items-center md:flex-row-reverse gap-6">
        <div class="w-72 md:w-80 ml-6">
          <HeroCard
            imageUrl="/assets/iconography/banderas-zorro.png"
            title="Zorro (1998)"
            link=""
          />
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1 flex justify-end">
          <div class="max-w-xl text-left md:text-right">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Hope</h3>
            <p
              class="text-base text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4 text-balance"
            >
              Zorro servers as a beacon of hope to the many who can not fight
              back against the Governor and his caballeros. Through his sly
              actions, Zorro is able to confront the corruption with cunning
              skill, creating a spectacle that inspires the people and puts fear
              into the heart of his enemies.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    class="mt-26 mb-12"
    data-aos="fade-up-sm"
    data-aos-delay="100"
    data-aos-duration="600"
    data-aos-once="true"
  >
    <div class="site-container px-4 md:px-8">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
        <div class="w-72 md:w-80 mr-6">
          <HeroCard
            imageUrl="/assets/iconography/lolita-and-zorro.png"
            title="Zorro and Lolita"
            link=""
          />
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Charm</h3>
          <p
            class="text-base text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4 text-balance"
          >
            Zorro and Don Diego both exude charisma that pierces through the screen. Zorro uses his charm to capture the love of Lolita in <em>The Mark of Zorro</em> (1940) and Elena in <em>The Mask of Zorro</em> (1998). Don Diego uses his charm to snake around the corrupt and cruel governors of Spanish California, all while maintaining his facade as a popinjay.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
